modules.description: This module enables the creation and sampling of probability distributions using the GSL random number generator, supporting a wide range of statistical distributions (e.g., Gaussian, Poisson, Dirichlet) over numerical types like `float`, `int`, and `bool`, as well as user-defined categorical types via hashtables. It facilitates probabilistic modeling tasks such as simulating stochastic processes, Bayesian inference, and generating synthetic datasets with complex distributional assumptions. The use of a shared RNG state ensures reproducibility in scenarios requiring coordinated random sampling across distributions.

This module implements probability distribution sampling with the GSL random number generator, supporting distributions like Gaussian, Poisson, and Dirichlet over numeric types and user-defined categorical types via hashtables. It enables probabilistic modeling tasks such as stochastic simulations, Bayesian inference, and synthetic dataset generation with precise control over distributional parameters. The module ensures reproducibility through a shared RNG state, coordinating random sampling across multiple distributions.
